According to BoT Monetary Policy Statement Mid-Year Review 2017/18, the interoperability among mobile payment services providers has contributed to substantial increase in transactions across network operators thus reducing the cost of mobile financial services. The transactions processed and their value represent 123.8 per cent and 92.7 per cent increase in volume and value, respectively, compared to transactions recorded during the similar period of the preceding year. The number of registered active accounts of mobile phone financial services was 19.3 million at the end of December last year, up from 17.02 million at the end of December 2016. The oversight and monitoring of the national payment systems in addition to licensing of new payment service providers including banks and non-banks continues to be carried out under the current regulatory framework